row.cell:
Item payde ffor ffetting a quarter malt
                      from wyndpolewyndpole: Wympole,
                          Cambridgeshire

First for the obsequies, 10d. On one quarter (and) one bushel of grain, 9s;
                    on milling and baking of the same, 12d; on six dozen (and) two kilderkins of
                    ale, 9s 9d; on two kilderkins of drink, 4d; on two calves, 4s; on two sheep, 4s
                    8d; on two lambs, 2s; on twenty-five geese, 4s 2d; on three coombs of oats, 22s;
                    on two bushels of oatmeal dust (ie, chaff), 3d; on four
                    dozen chicken pullets, 3s 4d; on milk and cream, 14d; on 150 eggs, 8 1/2d; on
                    butter, 3d; on salt, 1d; on onions, 1d; on vinegar and (malt ?) vinegar, 1d; on oatmeal, 1d; on honey, 3d; on various spices, 2s 10d;
                    on figs and raisins, 9d; on the stipends of two entertainers, 4s; on the stipend
                    of the cook, 16d; on fuel, 20d; on the turnspit, hastler, and servant, 10d; on a
                    cart for fish, namely, mackerel and eels and 'omy' for the cook, 4 1/2d.
